WEBVTT

1
00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:39.141
- Go. go. go. go!
- Move it. move it!

2
00:01:39.224 --> 00:01:40.851
- Let's go. let's go!
- Come on!

3
00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:42.978
It's a powder keg in there.

4
00:01:43.061 --> 00:01:45.439
No one moves
till we get word from the mayor.

5
00:01:58.702 --> 00:02:00.412
Shoot! Hey.

6
00:02:00.495 --> 00:02:01.705
Hey.

7
00:02:01.788 --> 00:02:03.123
Hey. Little girl.

8
00:02:03.749 --> 00:02:05.083
Stop.

9
00:02:05.167 --> 00:02:06.168
Stop!

10
00:02:08.587 --> 00:02:10.589
Stay down!

11
00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:23.060
What do you want. little one?

12
00:02:25.687 --> 00:02:26.938
Your ass.

13
00:02:52.923 --> 00:02:54.257
Boo!

14
00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:15.862
Well done.

15
00:03:36.425 --> 00:03:37.426
Who...

16
00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:39.094
who are you?

17
00:03:40.095 --> 00:03:42.347
Frank Drebin. Police Squad.

18
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.100
The new version.

19
00:04:03.535 --> 00:04:05.370
<i>Shoot. Um...</i>

20
00:04:16.465 --> 00:04:18.633
<i>My name is
Sergeant Frank Drebin.</i>

21
00:04:18.717 --> 00:04:20.594
<i>Detective Lieutenant. Police Squad.</i>

22
00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:23.263
<i>a special division of the LAPD.</i>

23
00:04:23.346 --> 00:04:26.475
<i>The day after the bank robbery
started like any other.</i>

24
00:04:26.558 --> 00:04:29.269
<i>I woke up in my empty cop apartment.</i>

25
00:04:29.352 --> 00:04:32.105
<i>stared at a picture
of my deceased cop wife</i>

26
00:04:32.189 --> 00:04:34.524
<i>and choked back cop tears.</i>

27
00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:36.777
<i>A perfect morning? Sure.</i>

28
00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:39.863
<i>But I had no idea
what this city had in store for me.</i>

29
00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:42.949
What the hell?

30
00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:46.828
- Hey!
- There he is.

31
00:04:46.912 --> 00:04:48.705
Way to go. Frank!

32
00:04:50.665 --> 00:04:52.167
Thank you. Thanks. everyone.

33
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:53.710
What is this?

34
00:04:53.794 --> 00:04:55.045
Don't cheer for him!

35
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:57.172
You two. my office now!

36
00:05:00.342 --> 00:05:03.136
Thanks to you.
I just spent two hours

37
00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:04.554
getting chewed out by the mayor.

38
00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:07.808
Apparently. some of
the bank robbers you put in the ICU.

39
00:05:07.891 --> 00:05:09.893
they're lawyering up to sue the city.

40
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.228
That's ridiculous.

41
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.355
- They're criminals.
- It's the law.

42
00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:15.524
Since when do cops
have to follow the law?

43
00:05:15.607 --> 00:05:17.025
- Since forever.
- Oh. yeah?

44
00:05:17.108 --> 00:05:19.361
And who's going to arrest me?
Other cops?

45
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:20.570
- Yes.
- Is she serious?

46
00:05:20.654 --> 00:05:22.113
Is he serious?

47
00:05:22.197 --> 00:05:23.448
He's... no.

48
00:05:23.532 --> 00:05:25.033
Look. let me be crystal clear.

49
00:05:25.116 --> 00:05:28.453
They are threatening to shut down
Police Squad because of you.

50
00:05:28.537 --> 00:05:30.997
Honestly. you're lucky
you still work here

51
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:33.124
after last year's McDonald's incident.

52
00:05:33.208 --> 00:05:35.210
They wouldn't sell me
Freedom Fries.

53
00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:37.546
You arrested the entire staff!

54
00:05:37.629 --> 00:05:38.713
I wasn't
thinking clearly.

55
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:42.259
I was furious about the
Janet Jackson Super Bowl.

56
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:44.261
That was 20 years ago!

57
00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:45.470
Not to me.

58
00:05:45.554 --> 00:05:47.389
We understand. Chief.
You're right.

59
00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:48.473
Good.

60
00:05:48.557 --> 00:05:50.308
'Cause I'm taking you
off the bank job.

61
00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:53.103
- What?
- I'm putting you on collisions.

62
00:05:53.186 --> 00:05:55.272
There's a crash up in Malibu.

63
00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.815
Yes. ma'am. Thank you.

64
00:05:56.898 --> 00:06:00.068
And make sure your bodycams
are actually turned on!

65
00:06:01.111 --> 00:06:03.780
Got it. Camera will be on.

66
00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:08.076
Drebin!

67
00:06:08.159 --> 00:06:10.453
It's a new day at Police Squad!

68
00:06:12.247 --> 00:06:15.125
Things are changing
so fast around here.

69
00:06:15.792 --> 00:06:17.961
I guess you really
can't fight City Hall. huh?

70
00:06:18.044 --> 00:06:19.629
No. It's a building.

71
00:06:20.797 --> 00:06:22.340
Now. there's a real man.

72
00:06:23.717 --> 00:06:25.927
They just don't make 'em
like your pops anymore.

73
00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:29.347
I'm glad he's not around
to see what Police Squad has come to.

74
00:06:30.390 --> 00:06:32.309
Mind if I take a minute. Ed?

75
00:06:32.392 --> 00:06:33.518
Of... of course.

76
00:06:37.689 --> 00:06:39.816
Hi. Daddy. It's me. Frank Jr.

77
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:42.861
I want to be just like you. but...

78
00:06:43.486 --> 00:06:46.948
at the same time.
be completely different and original.

79
00:06:47.032 --> 00:06:49.075
So. if you're proud of me.

80
00:06:49.743 --> 00:06:51.244
give me a sign. like...

81
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:54.748
maybe make me see an owl or something.

82
00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:57.500
Hey. Dad.

83
00:06:58.376 --> 00:06:59.794
It's me. Ed.

84
00:07:01.588 --> 00:07:03.131
Boy. do I miss you.

85
00:07:07.260 --> 00:07:08.428
Hey. Pops.

86
00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:12.015
Mm-mm.

87
00:07:16.227 --> 00:07:19.814
<i>Ed and I pulled up to
the Malibu car crash around 2:</i><i>00 p.m.</i>

88
00:07:20.315 --> 00:07:21.358
<i>Nothing unusual.</i>

89
00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:25.528
<i>But in this city.
usual is unusual... usually.</i>

90
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:26.613
What the hell?

91
00:07:29.074 --> 00:07:31.242
So how was your
date last night. Frank?

92
00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:33.745
Ah. I couldn't go through with it.

93
00:07:33.828 --> 00:07:35.288
- You canceled?
- Nope.

94
00:07:35.872 --> 00:07:36.873
I didn't want to upset her.

95
00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:40.085
so I had Officer Barnes
tell her I was stabbed to death.

96
00:07:40.168 --> 00:07:41.419
You're a real romantic. Frank.

97
00:07:41.503 --> 00:07:44.547
But everyone needs someone.
even a widower like you.

98
00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:47.550
I'm just not ready
to open myself to love again.

99
00:07:48.134 --> 00:07:50.637
I had them wait to clear
the wreck so you could get eyes on it.

100
00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:52.180
Crash happened around 4:00 a.m.

101
00:07:52.263 --> 00:07:54.766
Well. there are no skid marks
on the road.

102
00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:57.852
He didn't hit the brakes
before going over.

103
00:07:57.936 --> 00:07:59.020
Drunk?

104
00:07:59.104 --> 00:08:00.981
A little. Just enough to wake me up.

105
00:08:02.190 --> 00:08:03.191
Fancy car.

106
00:08:03.274 --> 00:08:06.277
Yeah. it's one
of those new EdenTech electric ones.

107
00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:07.821
Electric. huh?

108
00:08:07.904 --> 00:08:11.491
I remember when the only things
that were electric were eels. chairs.

109
00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:14.536
and Catherine Zeta-Jones in <i>Chicago.</i>

110
00:08:21.126 --> 00:08:22.419
Empty pill bottles.

111
00:08:32.679 --> 00:08:33.680
Huh.

112
00:08:38.476 --> 00:08:39.769
Who was he?

113
00:08:40.478 --> 00:08:42.897
Simon Davenport. 53 years old.

114
00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:44.649
No wife. no kids.

115
00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:46.401
He's got a sister out in Hancock Park.

116
00:08:46.484 --> 00:08:49.571
but we don't really know anything
about her other than her name.

117
00:08:49.654 --> 00:08:51.489
Beth Davenport.

118
00:08:51.573 --> 00:08:54.200
Divorced. 5'6". 130 pounds.

119
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:57.996
Spitfire of a personality.
Self-proclaimed chocoholic.

120
00:08:58.079 --> 00:09:00.582
Likes outdoorsy things
but is just as happy

121
00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:02.292
curling up with a good book.

122
00:09:02.917 --> 00:09:04.794
All right. I've seen enough.

123
00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:06.212
Mark it as suicide.

124
00:09:07.255 --> 00:09:08.256
Go ahead!

125
00:09:08.339 --> 00:09:09.549
Bring in the crane!

126
00:09:35.408 --> 00:09:37.243
- Oh. my God. it's up!
- Wait. I got to see what I got!

127
00:09:37.327 --> 00:09:39.079
- Yes. I got it!
- Come on. man!

128
00:09:39.162 --> 00:09:40.497
She can't even sing!

129
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.254
- Lieutenant?
- What's up. Barnes?

130
00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:49.964
Look. I know you're off
the bank job. sir.

131
00:09:50.048 --> 00:09:51.174
but I could really use your advice.

132
00:09:51.257 --> 00:09:53.384
- Go for it.
- Look. it's the strangest thing.

133
00:09:53.468 --> 00:09:55.053
All the thieves had never
met each other

134
00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:56.846
and none of them knew
who they were working for.

135
00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:58.348
Brilliant!

136
00:09:58.431 --> 00:10:00.767
If they don't know anything.
they can't squeal.

137
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:02.977
Whoever orchestrated
this is very smart.

138
00:10:03.061 --> 00:10:04.062
And get this.

139
00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:06.397
The robbers were told
that they could keep the cash.

140
00:10:06.481 --> 00:10:09.526
Who organizes a bank robbery
and doesn't keep the cash?

141
00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:11.444
They must have been
after something else.

142
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:13.655
Why don't you bring in
one of the perps?

143
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:15.031
See if we can get them talking.

144
00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:16.199
Got it. Thank you.

145
00:10:17.283 --> 00:10:19.577
Heads up. Frank. You got a visitor.

146
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.664
I told her to wait outside.
but she just walked in.

147
00:10:23.331 --> 00:10:24.582
You want me to get rid of her?

148
00:10:29.129 --> 00:10:30.171
No.

149
00:10:30.255 --> 00:10:31.714
That's okay. I'll deal with it.

150
00:10:40.765 --> 00:10:41.766
Oh.

151
00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:42.934
Over here. Lieutenant.

152
00:10:48.106 --> 00:10:50.316
<i>I'd sworn off love
after my wife died.</i>

153
00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:53.278
<i>but this woman was
put together in all the right ways.</i>

154
00:10:53.361 --> 00:10:56.447
<i>Face. head. shoulders. knees and toes.</i>

155
00:10:56.531 --> 00:10:58.408
<i>Knees and toes...</i>

156
00:10:58.491 --> 00:11:01.828
<i>and a bottom that would make
any toilet beg for the brown.</i>

157
00:11:04.164 --> 00:11:05.748
Sorry to keep you waiting. ma'am.

158
00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:08.585
How may I help you?

159
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:10.753
You're wrong about Simon Davenport.

160
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:12.714
He wouldn't commit suicide.

161
00:11:12.797 --> 00:11:14.257
Simon Davenport.

162
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:16.092
The stiff from the Malibu crash.

163
00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:17.844
That stiff was my brother.

164
00:11:18.469 --> 00:11:20.847
Oh. I mean...
he wasn't that stiff. really.

165
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:21.931
Not yet.

166
00:11:22.015 --> 00:11:23.474
More floppy and bloated.

167
00:11:24.058 --> 00:11:26.269
No. I mean.
I'm so sorry for your loss.

168
00:11:26.352 --> 00:11:27.645
Please. take a chair.

169
00:11:27.729 --> 00:11:29.105
No. thank you.

170
00:11:29.189 --> 00:11:30.690
I have plenty of chairs at home.

171
00:11:32.775 --> 00:11:35.111
Now. Mrs...

172
00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:36.196
Davenport.

173
00:11:36.821 --> 00:11:38.907
Miss Beth Davenport.

174
00:11:39.490 --> 00:11:41.326
- Mr.?
- Drebin.

175
00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:42.452
Miss...

176
00:11:43.036 --> 00:11:45.413
Detective Frank Drebin.

177
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.999
Detective. I think
someone murdered Simon.

178
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:50.001
Really? What makes you think that?

179
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:51.544
Well. he called me last night.

180
00:11:51.628 --> 00:11:52.921
He said he was in
some kind of trouble.

181
00:11:53.004 --> 00:11:55.089
So we made plans to meet this morning.

182
00:11:55.173 --> 00:11:57.842
Does that sound like someone
who's planning to kill themselves?

183
00:11:57.926 --> 00:12:00.053
No. it certainly does not.

184
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:02.388
Why would someone
do that to him?

185
00:12:04.766 --> 00:12:06.100
Trust me.

186
00:12:06.184 --> 00:12:08.519
there's always a reason
to kill someone.

187
00:12:08.603 --> 00:12:10.897
Did he have an obnoxious laugh?

188
00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:11.981
No.

189
00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:14.609
Forgive me. I'm just not myself.

190
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:16.653
That's okay. I'm not you. either.

191
00:12:19.072 --> 00:12:20.114
Tell me.

192
00:12:20.198 --> 00:12:22.075
what did your brother do for work?

193
00:12:22.158 --> 00:12:23.243
Computers.

194
00:12:23.993 --> 00:12:25.745
He was a programmer for Richard Cane.

195
00:12:25.828 --> 00:12:28.831
The genius who's gonna
save the world with his electric cars.

196
00:12:28.915 --> 00:12:30.583
Well. he's the first person
you should talk to.

197
00:12:30.667 --> 00:12:33.211
Then you could check Simon's
driving records and see if they match.

198
00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:34.379
Whoa. whoa. Slow down there.

199
00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:35.463
Excuse me?

200
00:12:35.546 --> 00:12:37.757
Let's just leave
the police work to me. okay?

201
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:40.677
Oh. I see.

202
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:42.387
Same old story with guys like you.

203
00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:43.596
Guys like me?

204
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:45.807
Stubborn old men who think
they know what's best.

205
00:12:49.185 --> 00:12:52.230
I understand you're upset.
but this is what I do.

206
00:12:52.313 --> 00:12:55.566
If someone did off your brother.
I'll find him.

207
00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:58.778
I appreciate that. Detective.
But Simon was all I had.

208
00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:01.114
So you'll forgive me
if I don't just sit around

209
00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:02.240
and hope you do your job.

210
00:13:02.323 --> 00:13:05.076
That's exactly what
I expect you to do.

211
00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:07.120
When I have something.
I'll contact you.

212
00:13:07.745 --> 00:13:09.914
I'm doing a series
of book readings this week.

213
00:13:09.998 --> 00:13:11.207
You can find me there.

214
00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:13.042
Book readings?

215
00:13:13.126 --> 00:13:14.252
Yes. I write true-crime novels

216
00:13:14.335 --> 00:13:16.254
based on fictional stories
that I make up.

217
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:19.882
Yes. well.

218
00:13:19.966 --> 00:13:21.801
you may write about it.

219
00:13:21.884 --> 00:13:22.969
but I live it.

220
00:13:24.220 --> 00:13:27.765
Now. if you'll excuse me.
we're having a birthday party

221
00:13:27.849 --> 00:13:30.059
and I'm the best singer in the office.

222
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:37.191
On second thought.
I will take that chair.

223
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:46.200
Whoa.

224
00:13:46.909 --> 00:13:48.286
<i>I couldn't
remember the last time</i>

225
00:13:48.369 --> 00:13:49.996
<i>someone had talked to me like that.</i>

226
00:13:50.621 --> 00:13:53.583
<i>It was the kind of dressing down
you usually have to pay for</i>

227
00:13:53.666 --> 00:13:55.501
<i>in the basement of a laundromat.
But she...</i>

228
00:13:55.585 --> 00:13:56.627
<i>She had the kind of hips</i>

229
00:13:56.711 --> 00:13:59.672
<i>you wanted to put a hula hoop
on and spin.</i>

230
00:13:59.756 --> 00:14:02.091
<i>The kind that made you...</i>

231
00:14:04.427 --> 00:14:05.470
Fellas. do you mind?

232
00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:14.771
<i>I wasn't convinced
Simon Davenport had been murdered.</i>

233
00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:17.357
<i>But the case was starting
to give me an itch.</i>

234
00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:19.108
<i>And when I start to scratch.</i>

235
00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:21.277
<i>I don't stop till I break skin</i>

236
00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.696
<i>and the doctor makes me wear mittens.</i>

237
00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:25.865
Thanks.

238
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:37.585
- Coat check?
- Champagne?

239
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:50.431
<i>Richard Cane had made
his first fortune in microprocessors.</i>

240
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:54.685
<i>and then used it to build
a vast online retail marketplace</i>

241
00:14:54.769 --> 00:14:56.854
<i>and green technology empire.</i>

242
00:15:00.817 --> 00:15:03.945
Then. suddenly.
the bear charges towards me.

243
00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:05.488
I ready my knife.

244
00:15:06.114 --> 00:15:07.532
and he barrels right past me

245
00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:10.034
to a honey hive above the campsite!

246
00:15:11.035 --> 00:15:13.121
It had been there all along!

247
00:15:13.204 --> 00:15:14.705
And I hadn't seen it.

248
00:15:21.379 --> 00:15:23.464
Ah. You've arrived.

249
00:15:24.882 --> 00:15:25.883
Lieutenant Drebin.

250
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:27.427
- Me. too!
- I'm Richar...

251
00:15:27.510 --> 00:15:28.970
Richard Cane.

252
00:15:29.554 --> 00:15:31.097
Please. walk with me.

253
00:15:32.223 --> 00:15:35.309
So. what can you tell me
about Mr. Davenport?

254
00:15:35.393 --> 00:15:37.186
Simon was a brilliant engineer.

255
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:38.396
and one of our best.

256
00:15:39.063 --> 00:15:41.524
I had no idea
